        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Union, or 7 miles northeast of Jonesville, moving east
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Saratt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
